description:
&lt;p&gt;As one of the largest acute Trusts in the UK – and with more than 20,000 employees – Manchester University NHS Foundation Trust (MFT) is on an exciting mission to deliver high-quality care to the people of Manchester, Trafford and beyond. Our vision is to create and deliver a seamless 24/7 service that extends beyond excellent care within our nine hospitals and community services within our Local Care Organisations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Senior Energy Officer is responsible for supporting the delivery of the Trust’s strategic approach to Energy Management including, but not limited to; environmental legal compliance, Energy Efficiency, sustainable design and construction, carbon strategy, energy efficiency auditing monitoring and evaluation and promoting corporate sustainability campaigns and staff engagement programmes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will proactively manage and monitor energy consumption throughout the Trust’s estate and ensure that the Trust fulfils its statutory &amp; best practice obligations in relation to energy management.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will work with energy suppliers to identify opportunities to reduce carbon emissions and reduce energy consumption and costs.&lt;/p&gt;
